351.Name: Wanderer's Trail
351.Desc: The god took away your only kin, and you were sealed and cast into a deep slumber. Upon your awakening, you wandered alone for a time until you met a strange companion named Paimon, thus beginning your journey through the continent of Teyvat...

352.Name: Bird's Eye View
352.Desc: You begin your journey in Starfell Valley, exploring the land and seeing its sights together with Paimon.

353.Name: Unexpected Power
353.Desc: As you advanced, a Statue of the Seven appeared on the horizon ahead of you. At Paimon's suggestion, you go to investigate.

355.Name: Forest Rendezvous
355.Desc: Unexpectedly, the power of Anemo within the Statue of the Seven resonated with you. You decided to begin your investigation with the Anemo Archon of Teyvat's Seven Archons. As such, the first order of the day is to reach the land under the Anemo Archon's protection: Mondstadt.

354.Name: Wind-Riding Knight
354.Desc: On the path to Mondstadt, you inadvertently eavesdropped on a meeting between a huge dragon and a mysterious figure. As you proceeded with various doubts in mind, a perky young girl showed up to block your path.

360.Name: Going Upon the Breeze
360.Desc: The girl's name is Amber, and her duty as an Outrider is to escort you to Mondstadt. However, she has another task to attend to first, which is to clean out the hilichurls that have been wandering around outside the city.

356.Name: City of Freedom
356.Desc: With your help, the problem was resolved quickly. Led by Amber, you reach the city of freedom — Mondstadt.

357.Name: Dragon Storm
357.Desc: The usually peaceful Mondstadt was suddenly assailed by a dragon. This is the Stormterror that Amber spoke of, and was the gigantic creature that you encountered in the forest earlier.

358.Name: Knights of Favonius
358.Desc: You repelled Stormterror with some difficulty. Kaeya of the Knights of Favonius witnessed the battle, and you were invited to make a trip to the Knights headquarters.

306.Name: Winds of the Past
306.Desc: To stop Stormterror's siege, you must venture out and eliminate the elemental flows left within the ruined Temples of the Four Winds. Amber is waiting for you at the Temple of the Falcon.

307.Name: Crash Course
307.Desc: Kaeya will accompany you to explore the Temple of the Wolf.

308.Name: Sparks Amongst the Pages
308.Desc: Lisa is in charge of clearing the Temple of the Lion alongside you.

311.Name: First Stage Ended
311.Desc: After completing the first stage, talk to Paimon for a hidden quest

370.Name: Shadow Over Mondstadt
370.Desc: Thanks to your efforts, Mondstadt's elemental flow has returned to normal. It's time to report back to Jean.

371.Name: Unexpected Encounter
371.Desc: Returning to Mondstadt, you encountered a clash between Jean and the Fatui. Afterward, you showed Jean the dragon tear that you found in the forest, and at her request, once again joined the investigation into Stormterror Dvalin.

372.Name: That Green Fellow
372.Desc: As you were heading out to investigate, you happened upon the mysterious guy that you saw talking to the dragon.

373.Name: Let the Wind Lead
373.Desc: The mysterious fellow claimed to be a bard named Venti, but left on his own accord before you could get him to explain his relationship with the dragon. You follow him to the giant tree at Windrise.

374.Name: Venti's Plan
374.Desc: Stopped at last, Venti explained that he had tried and failed to cleanse Dvalin's curse during their previous meeting. Now, he has been forced to rely on the Holy Lyre der Himmel's power if he is to restore Dvalin.

375.Name: Venti's New Plan
375.Desc: Venti's plan to sweet talk his way into getting the Holy Lyre back backfires. He's come up with a new plan, but seems he'll need your help for it to work.

376.Name: Wild Escape
376.Desc: Venti's plan to steal the Holy Lyre went off without a hitch. Well, almost — when the Lyre was almost in your hands, a stranger stole it from under your noses. Your movements alerted the guards, forcing you to flee the Cathedral.

377.Name: Behind the Scenes
377.Desc: In your haste fleeing from the confusion, you found yourself in Diluc's tavern, where — to your surprise — he decided to help hide you. Diluc agrees to meet back at the tavern after nightfall with his "contacts" — who could they be?

20101.Name: Chasing Shadows
20101.Desc: The person Diluc called in turned out to be Jean from the Knights of Favonius. After some discussions, it is discovered that it was the Fatui who stole the Holy Lyre der Himmel. You must retrieve it to rescue Dvalin.

379.Name: State of the Holy Lyre der Himmel
379.Desc: After a fierce battle, you managed to seize the Holy Lyre der Himmel back from the hands of the Fatui. For some reason, Venti seems to express a great nostalgia for the Lyre...

385.Name: Let's go on an Adventure
385.Desc: The Adventurers' Guild can give you Adventure Reports on the area surrounding Mondstadt. All reports are free!

380.Name: Fallen Tears
380.Desc: The Holy Lyre is in poor condition, but you manage to restore some of its Anemo power by using Dvalin's tears. To restore its full power, you will need to look for more tears.

381.Name: Hidden Tears
381.Desc: Dvalin's footprints are all over Mondstadt, and one of his tears fell upon a ruin deep within the forest.

382.Name: Stolen Tears
382.Desc: The corrupted dragon tear has even attracted hilichurls. You must get it back from them.

383.Name: Crystal Tears
383.Desc: After completing the retrieval of the tears, you meet up with the rest of the group.

384.Name: Reunion with the Dragon
384.Desc: Dvalin's tears restored the Holy Lyre back to its full power. Now, you are finally ready to purify Stormterror.

397.Name: Abyss Mage
397.Desc: You used the Holy Lyre der Himmel to summon Stormterror, only to be prevented from saving it due to the interference of the Abyss Order. But you haven't given up yet — and Diluc has been able to swiftly obtain a new lead...

388.Name: Hurdle
388.Desc: You came to Stormterror's Lair to once again attempt Dvalin's rescue. However, it is surrounded by wind barriers made by Stormterror, and the dark forces at work have no intention of letting you break through those barriers so easily.

389.Name: Empty Abode
389.Desc: Assailed by many enemies, you realize that this road will not be an easy one. The way into Stormterror's Lair is strewn with obstacles, and so you must proceed with caution to find a path along the ruined walls.

390.Name: Light Guiding Ceremony
390.Desc: The entrance to Stormterror's Lair is just ahead, but the light seals bar the way in. You must once again face a trial in order to break those seals.

393.Name: Calm Before the Storm
393.Desc: The three light seals have each been broken by you in their turn, and the path to the decisive showdown is open. You once again return to the lair's entrance to put an end to things.

394.Name: A Long Shot
394.Desc: After a long and daring pursuit of Dvalin, who has been led astray by the Abyss Mages, you are about to finally confront him once and for all.

398.Name: When the Wind Dies Down
398.Desc: You finally managed to save Dvalin. Is this where the story of the wind ends?

396.Name: Ending Note
396.Desc: Amber says that Jean is waiting for you at the Cathedral. Apparently, it's something to do with the Holy Lyre der Himmel...

407.Name: Liyue Game
407.Desc: A mysterious man calling himself the Cricket Referee excitedly invites you to play a game popular with the masses in Liyue.

408.Name: Pontoon Parkour
408.Desc: At Cider Lake, a woman explained her troubles to you.

409.Name: Slime Baskets
409.Desc: An enthusiastic slime breeder invites you to play with them.

418.Name: Break the Sword Cemetery Seal
418.Desc: According to Dr. Livingstone, there are three hilichurl tribes surrounding the Sword Cemetery in <color=00E1FFFF>Dadaupa Gorge**. To the north, the Meaty tribe; to the south, the Sleeper tribe; and in the valley to the east, the Eclipse tribe. The key to breaking the seals on the Sword Cemetery may lie within their encampments...

419.Name: Break the Eclipse Tribe's Seal
419.Desc: The Eclipse tribe's Elemental Monument stands at the center of their dilapidated altar. It is being defended by samachurls, mitachurls and Abyss Mages, so it might be best to find a way to pick them off.

420.Name: Break the Sleeper Seal
420.Desc: The Sleeper tribe's power lies beneath a large tree, defended by mitachurls and a heap of hilichurls. Defeating mitachurls will break the seal on the Elemental Monument. It is said that mitachurls sleep early, so surprising them at night might be a good idea.

422.Name: Break the Meaty Seal
422.Desc: The Meaty tribe worships power. Challenge them in the arena to break the seal.

423.Name: Find the Missing Fairy
423.Desc: The fairies were kidnapped by nearby hilichurls, devastating the Tree of Life. If we manage to save the fairies, perhaps the Tree of Life will respond to our prayers.

451.Name: Wolves' Territory
451.Desc: You and Paimon decide to pay a visit to Wolvendom, a place in Mondstadt that few people pass through, without any knowledge of the dangers that may await you within this primordial territory.

452.Name: Another Day as an Outrider!
452.Desc: On your last legs from being attacked by an enormous slime, you were rescued by a young man named Razor. Razor, who calls a wolf pack family, mentioned a "red one, burny girl." You have your guesses as to who that is...

453.Name: Ravaged by Wolves
453.Desc: It seems that the "red, burny girl" was not Amber, as you had thought. But you receive news from Amber about wolf pack attacks in Drunkard Gorge. The wolf pack, the boy, the attacks... things are getting more complicated. This calls for a thorough investigation.

454.Name: Fate's Chosen Lupical
454.Desc: You are yet again led to Wolvendom. Are these Wolfhook seeds solid evidence? Are Razor and his wolf pack really behind the attack? Or are the Wolfhooks indicative of something else?

461.Name: Kaeya's Troubles
461.Desc: You bump into Kaeya, whom you first met during Stormterror's attack, at the Knights of Favonius Headquarters.

462.Name: Mystery of the Arcadian Ruins
462.Desc: According to Kaeya, his pirate grandfather left behind a treasured sword that has been buried in the Lost Arcadian Ruins. To prevent it from falling into the wrong hands, you search high and low for intelligence regarding the ruins.

463.Name: Kaeya's Gain
463.Desc: After much thinking, you finally solve the riddles contained within the intel you were given. The Lost Arcadian Ruins are now within reach!

464.Name: Legend of the Darknight Hero
464.Desc: Recently, rumors about a certain Darknight Hero have been circulating around Mondstadt...

465.Name: Darknight Hero's Crisis
465.Desc: Your inquiries were slowly bringing the Darknight Hero's identity to light, but just then, you met the man himself. His true identity is Diluc, owner of the Dawn Winery — and his actions have long since attracted the attention of the Knights of Favonius...

466.Name: Darknight Hero's Alibi
466.Desc: Knight Huffman has informed you that the Abyss Order is plotting against the Darknight Hero. As a precaution, the Knights have decided to monitor the Darknight Hero's actions. You shared this information with Diluc and discussed countermeasures. Having made your preparations, you now lie in wait for both the Knights and the Abyss Order to act.

467.Name: The Art of Cooking
467.Desc: On the outskirts of the city of Mondstadt, the adventurer Lynn is currently preparing to make a meal...

468.Name: The Boars are Attacking!
468.Desc: Boars keep attacking the vineyards, and Tunner is getting anxious...

469.Name: The Blessings of The Seven
469.Desc: Paimon suggests you go to a Statue of The Seven.

470.Name: Scent on the Wind
470.Desc: As you walk through Mondstadt, Paimon is attracted by the aroma of food...

481.Name: Glide with the Wind
481.Desc: Amber wishes to discuss the matter of how you've been using your wind glider...

480.Name: License to Glide
480.Desc: Amber has specially prepared a gliding exam for you. She has also provided a gliding manual, which she has asked you to read before taking the exam.

427.Name: Mondstadt Glider
427.Desc: As it turned out, the book Amber gave you wasn't a manual, but a fairy tale... After completing the first test out in the wild, you learn that the second test is to take place within the city of Mondstadt itself. Amber is waiting for you there.

484.Name: They Call Him Raptor
484.Desc: During the exam, you were mistaken for the thief Raptor by Otto, a Knight of Favonius, and were stopped. After clearing the misunderstanding, you volunteer to help arrest Raptor — and so begins the chase.

485.Name: Outrider Style
485.Desc: During your pursuit, you track Raptor to his hideout. You plunge into its depths without hesitation. Time to bring this criminal to justice.

486.Name: When the West Wind Arises
486.Desc: Sara from the Good Hunter restaurant appears to have a request for the Knights of Favonius...

487.Name: Margaret's Longing
487.Desc: While Jean is ill from overwork, you've been tasked with handling some citizens' commissions on her behalf. Where has Margaret's pet cat Prince run off to this time?

488.Name: Charles' Troubles
488.Desc: Has Charles managed to get hold of the tax forms he needs?

489.Name: Sara's Worries
489.Desc: Sara's delivery of ingredients still hasn't arrived, and she's growing more anxious by the minute...

490.Name: Master's Day Off
490.Desc: Today's commissions are done and dusted. Time to check up on Jean at the Cathedral.

1000.Name: Rite of Descension
1000.Desc: In the land of Liyue by the sea, a city sits atop the solid bedrock. That city is Liyue Harbor, and it has flourished under the protection of its guardian Morax — also known as "Rex Lapis," the Geo Archon you have been looking for. You could not have arrived at a more fortuitous time, as the annual "Rite of Descension" has just begun. Every year on this day, Rex Lapis graces this land with his prophecy, giving guidance on the economic path Liyue should follow in the coming year.

1002.Name: An Impromptu Change of Plan
1002.Desc: During the rite, the appointed moment arrived. Yet when the clouds parted, a divine carcass crashed down to earth, knocking all the offerings over. Amid the chaos and confusion, the Qixing ordered that the assassin be arrested. Unable to prove your innocence, you were forced to accept the help of Childe of the Fatui, and as suggested by him, you are now headed for Jueyun Karst, a hidden abode where the adepti dwell...

1003.Name: Wangshu
1003.Desc: You came across an adeptus, "Moon Carver." Seeing the keepsake you bore, he lent you his aid and protected you from the Millelith soldiers pursuing you. Upon learning of Rex Lapis' passing and the unjust accusations laid against you, Moon Carver expressed disdain for the Qixing's actions and began to suspect that they were behind what happened. He has sent you to find several other adepti and deliver a message to them.

1008.Name: Moulder of Mountains
1008.Desc: Following the instructions of Moon Carver, you arrive at Mt. Hulao in order to meet with Mountain Shaper.

1009.Name: Custodian of Clouds
1009.Desc: Following Moon Carver's instructions, you arrive at Mt. Aocang in order to seek out Cloud Retainer.

1018.Name: Dust to Dust
1018.Desc: Having sought out the adepti and completed the task Moon Carver entrusted to you, you return again to Liyue Harbor to look for Childe. He tells you that the Liyue Qixing's response to the archon's passing has given him some food for thought...

1010.Name: An Organization Known as Wangsheng
1010.Desc: Upon your return from visiting the Adepti, you discover that the Qixing have hidden the Geo Archon's vessel away. Childe promised he'd find someone to break the stalemate, so you pay another visit to Northland Bank.

1011.Name: Moonfinger
1011.Desc: Childe introduced you to Zhongli, a consultant at Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. You agree to help Zhongli organize the Rite of Parting in the hope of seeing the Geo Archon again.

1012.Name: Three Poignant Perfumes
1012.Desc: Zhongli isn't concerned with the deicide itself, but with upholding Liyue's sacred traditions by giving a proper farewell to an archaic lord. Having selected a suitable batch of Noctilucous Jade, your next task is to prepare some perfumes as an offering to the Geo Archon.

1014.Name: The Realm Within
1014.Desc: After identifying Rex Lapis' preferred scent, Zhongli sends you to Yujing Terrace to seek out an old friend of his, Madame Ping, and borrow a certain Cleansing Bell. Strange... Zhongli seems to be avoiding his old friend...

1013.Name: Downtown
1013.Desc: Who would have guessed — Madame Ping is an adeptus! After leaving her household, which turned out to be a realm within a teapot, you proceed to Chihu Rock to continue preparations.

1015.Name: Guizhong
1015.Desc: You came to renowned purveyor of Liyue herbal medicine, Bubu Pharmacy, to procure some Everlasting Incense. But what started out as a straightforward trip to the pharmacy has turned into a far more complicated affair...

1016.Name: Zhongli's Treat
1016.Desc: That Bubu Pharmacy trip turned into quite an exhilarating ride. (Okay, maybe not that exhilarating.) In yet another remarkable twist, Zhongli has offered to treat you to dinner!

1020.Name: The Floating Palace
1020.Desc: The mysterious emissary Ganyu appeared before you at Third-Round Knockout. Claiming to have come at Ningguang's behest, she invited you to the skyfaring palace known as the Jade Chamber. To that end, you and Paimon have come to Mt. Tianheng, from where you can see the Jade Chamber in the distance.

1021.Name: Equilibrium
1021.Desc: After arriving at the Guizhong Ballista on Mt. Tianheng, you are surprised to meet another member of the Qixing there. Her name is Keqing, and she gives you detailed instructions on how to ascend to the Jade Chamber. Paimon, however, is preoccupied with another detail that Keqing mentioned: the custom of bringing a greeting gift.

1022.Name: Solitary Fragrance
1022.Desc: You finally ascended to the Jade Chamber, where Ningguang was waiting for you. She graciously accepted Paimon's gift, and offered one in return. You spoke at length about many things: deities, archons... and the Fatui...

1023.Name: Heart of Glaze
1023.Desc: At Ningguang's advice, you verified the Fatui's schemes regarding the Sigil of Permission before continuing to help Zhongli prepare for the rite. You met Ganyu once again at Dihua Marsh before returning to Liyue Harbor — only to find that things in the city seem to be spiraling out of control.

1024.Name: Turning Point
1024.Desc: The adepti faced off against the Qixing outside the city. Just as things were coming to a head, you went to the Golden House to intercept Childe as he attempted to seize the Gnosis, only to find yet another twist: The Gnosis was never at the Golden House to begin with. Childe swiftly switched to his backup plan, attempting to force the Geo Archon to make an appearance by summoning an ancient god with Fatui-forged Sigils of Permission...

1025.Name: The Fond Farewell
1025.Desc: The ancient god was subdued once again following a fierce battle and much sacrifice. The dust settles, and your journey in Liyue is reaching its conclusion with the Rite of Parting. But before that, there are still some mysteries regarding the Geo Archon that need unraveling.

10100.Name: Troublesome Work
10100.Desc: Librarian Lisa seems annoyed about her work...

10101.Name: Lost Book
10101.Desc: Many people forget to return the library books they've borrowed, leaving Lisa no choice but to chase them and retrieve the books. Marjorie and Sara have agreed to return the books they borrowed as soon as possible, but Donna's seems to have been stolen. You decide to track the missing book down by following the trail left by an elemental marking Lisa made on it.

10110.Name: A Child's Secret
10110.Desc: At the feet of the Anemo Archon Statue in the plaza in front of Mondstadt Cathedral, you and Paimon discover a little girl playing with her imaginary friend...

10111.Name: The South Wind Brings Adventure
10111.Desc: While investigating imaginary friends with Venti, Ellin asked you to search for the adventurer Jack within the Temple of the Lion. It seems he is traveling together with the legendary adventurer, Stanley.

10112.Name: Lionfang's Legacy
10112.Desc: Jack wants to search for Stanley's old weapons in secret, as they are the sword and shield passed down from the Lion of the South, and thus fascinate Jack greatly.

10113.Name: Should You Be Trapped in a Windless Land
10113.Desc: Jack returns home satisfied after a round of adventure. But Venti finds Stanley's behavior odd, and decides to investigate further...

10200.Name: Who is Mondstadt's Strongest Fighter?
10200.Desc: Customers at the Angel's Share have started debating the hottest topic on Mondstadt's streets: "Who is the strongest fighter in Mondstadt?"

10201.Name: The Mystery of the Girl in Red's Treasure
10201.Desc: You have heard people from various corners weigh in on who the strongest fighter in Mondstadt is, but have yet to get a definite answer. Outside the Knights headquarters, you have an unexpected meeting with one of the candidates for the title — Klee, who is in dire need of help to recover her stolen treasure.

10202.Name: A Very Volatile Treasure
10202.Desc: Klee's highly explosive "treasure" proved to be a remarkably swift solution to the Abyss Mage problem. However, she fled the scene after the explosion. Confused, you decide to return to the Knights headquarters and report the matter to Jean...

10300.Name: （test）芭芭拉线玩法白盒
10300.Desc: （test）现在是芭芭拉线的玩法白盒，白盒完成后会转为芭芭拉线。

11000.Name: Little Chef on a Hunt
11000.Desc: On a clear and sunny day, you go for a walk to Springvale with Paimon.

11001.Name: Cooking Appointment
11001.Desc: While out on a stroll, you bumped into a strange girl. This girl, a chef from Liyue by the name of Xiangling, is on a journey to seek out exotic ingredients. She enlists your help in a hunt, but your private hunting expedition appears to have earned the ire of Draff, the leader of the hunters. You head off to apologize to him...

11002.Name: Secret Ingredient
11002.Desc: To your surprise, Draff did not intend to reprimand Xiangling, but instead wanted her to help promote Springvale's meat products instead. Sticking to her principles, Xiangling refused to cook for advertising, and would have left if she was not attracted to the smell of Brook's cooking. What began as a chat devolved into disagreement about how to prepare food, and ended in the declaration of a cook-off between the head chef of Springvale and the chef from Liyue.

11003.Name: Lucky Find
11003.Desc: Xiangling believes that Lotus Heads and Jueyun Chilies alone will not let her prevail in the cook-off, and sets off to find more ingredients.

11004.Name: Present from the Past
11004.Desc: Xiangling took a keen interest in the rumor that the ruins contain a gigantic Cryo Regisvine, and ran inside to investigate. Worried about her safety, you quickly follow the impetuous chef.

11005.Name: Cooking Showdown
11005.Desc: After obtaining the rare ingredients, Xiangling is finally ready for the cook-off. The showdown between the two head chefs is about to begin.

40001.Name: Towards the Lanterns Origin
40001.Desc: Every year, on the day of the first full moon, the Lantern Rite of Liyue takes place. On that night, everyone in Liyue releases Xiao Lanterns and Mingxiao Lanterns into the bright night sky. Within each of the xiao lanterns, placed a natural levitation stone, and on it hung one's wishful prayer, or a painting depicting one's desire. The lanterns slowly fly away while carrying a hope that the lights emitted by the lanterns might guide the soul of once Liyue's faithful protector, to return and reunite once more. You and Paimon have arrived at this solemn moment of Liyue, preparing for your five-days-long journey...

40002.Name: Water Beneath the Lanterns Flows Deep
40002.Desc: The most awaited moment of the Lantern Rite is the time when a giant Mingxiao Lantern released into the sky on the night of the fifth day. And the size of the Mingxiao Lantern this year is a sight that you don't want to miss, as the levitation stone used to make the giant lantern float this year is the biggest in 20 years. On this special occasion, the merchants of Liyue have prepared a Xiao Market, which was built using the same materials as the lanterns. When you arrived at the Xiao Market, the event organizer Huixin asked you for a favor...

40003.Name: In the City of Geo Live the Adepti
40003.Desc: Materials which are used to make lanterns are all easily flammable, and they're piling up at Liyue's port. Between the mountains of materials, you saw a mysterious figure, which shortly got annoyed by your presence and told you off. You and Paimon shared a look and stared at the piles of wood, paper, and oil... You have a bad feeling about this and you went to the Ministry of Civil Affairs to report the situation. Now you're wondering how they're handling the situation, and you've decided to go and see.

40004.Name: To My Old Friend, Wind Brings My Greetings
40004.Desc: After receiving your help, Millelith is finally able to assign a little group to reinforce their defenses around the city. Unsatisfied with the lack of effort from them, you've come back to the area hoping to find more clues. To your surprise, you met Xiao, a Liyue adeptus who also has the same intention as you. You both discovered that there are some markings at the corners of the construction site. "If a shackle within the realm of deities and demons got loose, I shall take full responsibility." "But this time, the threat comes from the mortal world —— your world, and thus, you shall take full responsibility, mortal traveler." said the adeptus to you. To decipher the markings and to learn its origin, you're reminded of that person that you've met in Mondstadt, a knight who prioritizes results above all else without caring about every trivial law...

40005.Name: Lanterns in the Sea
40005.Desc: Through Kaeya's informant, you found out that it's a kind of communication marking used by the Treasure Thieves, a criminal organization spanning across Teyvat. It seems this whole thing is not as serious as you originally thought. The Treasure Thieves in Liyue just received an anonymous letter. Out of fear and respect for Xiao, the Treasure Thieves gave the letter to you. The sender requested that someone of high rank from the Treasure Thieves meet with them secretly in Liyue to discuss an important matter. Once again, out of fear and respect for Xiao, they agreed to let you play as a high ranking official of the Treasure Thieves and meet the mysterious sender.

Zhongli is roped in as a consultant, along with an archaeologist named Wanyan who volunteers for the task. Though you distrust the Fatui, you join up at Zhongli's invitation. The first subject of this investigation is Osial, Overlord of the Vortex.

11022.Name: A Ruin Under Lock and Key

Kliment and Wanyan also clashed vociferously over their differing perspectives, which has greatly displeased the former. During the argument, he heard Wanyan mention the tale of the God of Salt, and decided to take the party there to try their luck, lest he finishes this venture empty-handed.

11023.Name: Farewell, Sweet Salt

11024.Name: A Record of All Things
11024.Desc: Within the ruins, Kliment and Wanyan each betray the contract in turn for personal reasons. As punishment, Kliment is cast out of the ruin and deprived of his reward. Wanyan is made to witness a truth that shatters her beliefs — the God of Salt was gentle but weak and was betrayed and slain as a result. Bearing witness to this incident and filled with conflicted feelings as a result, you follow Zhongli back to Guyun Stone Forest.

11031.Desc: Caught between the world of humans and adepti, Ganyu has descended into a funk. After she hits a snag in her plan to return to Jueyun Karst, you follow Ganyu back to Liyue Harbor, intending to resolve her misunderstanding that she has been dismissed from her post...

11032.Name: A Pact That Crosses Time
11032.Desc: Accepting the commission of the Tianshu, Uncle Tian, Ganyu very naturally slips into her work mode, coming to the aid of her junior colleague Huixin with ease in the latter's time of need. To express her thanks, Huixin invites you all to Xinyue Kiosk to have a meal...

11040.Name: The Rumored Alchemist
11040.Desc: You arrive at Timaeus' alchemy store in Mondstadt one day to stock up on adventuring supplies. But here, you encounter someone altogether unexpected...

11041.Name: The Genius Researcher and the Seed of Another World
11041.Desc: While searching for Albedo, you encounter an odd-looking sister named Rosaria. She claims to know where Albedo is and expresses her willingness to show you the way.

11042.Name: The First Experiment: Elements
11042.Desc: After finding Albedo, Rosaria leaves on her own. You chat with Albedo and discover the objective of his research: to use alchemy to cause a seed from another world to sprout and flourish. To better understand otherworldly lifeforms, Albedo states his desire to observe you and to perform some experiments in the process.

11043.Name: The Third Experiment: Life
11043.Desc: After the elemental flow tests, Albedo asks you to display any special, otherworldly abilities you may have, though nothing comes of this. Still, Albedo's interest in you has not waned in the least...

11044.Name: The Second Experiment: The World
11044.Desc: After the experiment begins, Albedo first checks your elemental flow. The result is that both your internal and external elemental flows run smoothly and that there is nothing unusual about them. These results seem very normal indeed, but according to Albedo, this is something to be happy about.

11045.Name: The Final Experiment: Withering Glory
11045.Desc: As the experiments proceed, Albedo obtains more and more data related to you, and the alchemy he envisages begins to take shape. Finally, after a simple test of your physical capabilities, the experiments draw to a close...

11110.Name: The Mysterious Wangsheng Parlor
11110.Desc: Your adventure takes you to Wuwang Hill, where Paimon senses that something is amiss...

11111.Name: In Pursuit of a Phantom
11111.Desc: When you agreed to help Hu Tao and followed her to the Adventurers' Guild, you hadn't counted on becoming part of Wangsheng Funeral Parlor's "business development" efforts. No topic is too sensitive for Hu Tao — certainly not matters of life and death — and even though some of her points make sense, you find them somewhat difficult to stomach. Then, when you voice your doubts about her approach, she tells you that she has long since moved on from business development to her next objective: finding someone called "Big G."

11112.Name: Friendships, Wishes, and Regrets
11112.Desc: Meng tells you that Big G is his childhood friend, who died by misadventure. Filled with regret and worry, Meng believes that due to a supernatural turn of events, Big G has become an evil spirit. Luocheng, another superstitious person who believes in ghost stories just like Meng, visits the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor seeking an exorcism. However, Hu Tao knows that the source of their worries is imaginary, so she comes up with an equally make-believe solution and organizes a fake exorcism. Surprisingly, the spirit of Big G appears before your eyes after the ritual.

11113.Name: Perfect Send-Off
11113.Desc: It turns out that Big G's spirit was attracted by the exorcism. Upon learning that Big G has not become a malevolent spirit and simply wanted to check on Meng and other childhood friends, Hu Tao decides to fulfill his wish and organize a farewell ceremony for him. To give him peace of mind, you collect keepsakes and well-wishes that Big G's childhood friends prepared for him. The only thing left now is to send him off.

18000.Name: Bough Keeper: Dainsleif
18000.Desc: Katheryne of the Mondstadt Adventurers' Guild seems to have something to tell you.

19001.Name: Sister Victoria's Vexation
19001.Desc: Sister Victoria seems to be troubled by something...

19002.Name: Sudden Shouting
19002.Desc: Someone suddenly starts calling for Barbara in Wolvendom...

19003.Name: The Church's Affairs
19003.Desc: At Barbara's request, you head back to Mondstadt to report to Sister Victoria.

19004.Name: The First Chilibrew Ingredient
19004.Desc: To make some Chilibrew, Barbara has asked you to look for some fresh Jueyun Chilis near the Stone Gate.

19005.Name: Knight and Deaconess, Ready for Battle!
19005.Desc: Repel the Treasure Hoarders and rescue the merchant being threatened by them.

19006.Name: The Second Chilibrew Ingredient
19006.Desc: To make some Chilibrew, you prepare to go with Barbara to the Whispering Woods to look for some Sweet Flowers.

19008.Name: Healing Is My Job
19008.Desc: To heal Uwe, you accompany Barbara to search the Whispering Woods for Small Lamp Grass.

19009.Name: A Very Special Beverage
19009.Desc: After helping to clean up the Cathedral, you get ready to meet Barbara at The Cat's Tail.

19021.Name: Hard to Track
19021.Desc: As you approach the wharf of Liyue Harbor, an unusually-dressed young man comes up to you, asking after some really strange business...

19022.Name: Distant Gaze
19022.Desc: The young thaumaturge Chongyun has obtained a great amount of (rather unreliable-sounding) information concerning evil spirits. He seems a little dejected when you point this out. As he uses a popsicle to suppress his pure-yang spirit, you both feel someone's gaze on you from the side.

19023.Name: The Exorcist's Path
19023.Desc: Dalong leaves after having been given half the popsicles, feeling quite pleased. After this small interlude, you and Chongyun continue discussing evil spirits. Chongyun hopes to tap on your abundant experience as an adventurer to adjudge the truth or falsehood of information concerning evil spirits. To that end, you head to Wanwen Bookhouse together.

19024.Name: Popsicles and Their Curious Uses
19024.Desc: Dalong leaves after having been given all the popsicles, feeling most pleased. For Chongyun, these popsicles are essential to suppressing his pure-yang spirit, and so he must have some on his person at any given time. The two of you head to Wanmin Restaurant to restock.

19025.Name: For A Child's Smile
19025.Desc: Chongyun's mind is still on that kid named Dalong even after you've made some more popsicles. The two of you head to Chihu Rock, intending to give the new popsicles to him as well.

19030.Name: Test of Courage
19030.Desc: The young thaumaturge Chongyun has obtained a great amount of (rather unreliable-sounding) information concerning evil spirits, but you decide not to expose this fact out of courtesy. The way Chongyun sees it, the most likely spot for evil spirits to show up is Wuwang Hill, where a Test of Courage is currently taking place. The test requires two people to go in together, so you accept his invitation and accompany him there...

19031.Name: Sudden Discomfort
19031.Desc: You and Chongyun successfully enter the Test of Courage, but as you track the evil spirits, Chongyun suddenly experiences a rush of unstable yang energy and must rest. To prevent his constitution from going out of control, you look for something that might help suppress his pure-yang spirit...

19032.Name: Independent Actions
19032.Desc: Chongyun's pure-yang spirit has finally been brought under control, but he is now aware that the strange goings-on during the Test of Courage are a result of human activity. However, neither of you is ready to give up yet, and at Chongyun's suggestion, you split up and continue to search for traces of the paranormal...

19033.Name: Ever Deeper
19033.Desc: You and Chongyun successfully enter the Test of Courage, and despite causing a misunderstanding, you also gain knowledge of evil spirits. The two of you proceed deeper, equal parts expectant and cautious.

19034.Name: The Bottom of Things
19034.Desc: You and Chongyun successfully enter the Test of Courage, but as you track the evil spirits, Chongyun suddenly experiences a rush of unstable yang energy and must rest. But it would be a shame to leave without having found any evil spirits. And so you forge on alone, leaving Chongyun behind to rest.

19035.Name: Killjoy
19035.Desc: After a conversation with the Test of Courage staff, you discover that the spooky things happening there are all instigated by humans. While you expected as much, you imagine that Chongyun would be quite disappointed if you told him so...

19041.Name: Adventurous Acquaintance
19041.Desc: You make the acquaintance of a rather passionate adventurer at the front desk of the Mondstadt Adventurers' Guild...

19042.Name: Something... Other Than Adventure?
19042.Desc: You agree to travel with Bennett, but you're doing some things unrelated to adventure this time — for example... running around the city?

19043.Name: What Is This, a Day Trip?
19043.Desc: You agree to travel with Bennett, but you're doing some things unrelated to adventure this time — for example... having a stroll in the great outdoors?

19044.Name: Treacherous Thermadon
19044.Desc: You should only go adventuring after making sure that you're fully prepared! You and Bennett prepare some food before you challenge the Deserted Ruins of Thermadon.

19045.Name: Expansive Eya
19045.Desc: An adventurer requires naught but courage and strength. The two of you prepare to head directly to the Deserted Ruins of Eya.

19061.Name: Maid-in-Training
19061.Desc: In accordance with your growing fame as the Honorary Knight, one of your junior Knights of Favonius would like to receive your guidance...

19062.Name: The Art of Hospitality
19062.Desc: You and Noelle met a strange guest near Mondstadt named Alois. Alois claims to be a merchant who has lost his cargo due to a monster attack. Noelle decides to bring Alois to Mondstadt to help him find his lost goods...

19064.Name: Noelle's Strength
19064.Desc: Noelle, who aims to become a Knight of Favonius, has shared her troubles with you and hopes that you'll be able to help her with her chivalric training. To display the fruits of her daily training to her, Noelle takes you to the Knights' training ground...

19065.Name: Live Practice
19065.Desc: Noelle has great strength but is never able to use it in real fights. You arrange some training to help her gain more practical combat experience...

19066.Name: Strength Training
19066.Desc: Noelle has great strength, but the path to greater strength is never-ending. Your suggestion to help her bring out yet more power is... mining.

19067.Name: Fleeting Leisure
19067.Desc: Noelle, who aims to become a Knight of Favonius, has shared her troubles with you and hopes that you'll be able to help her with her chivalric training. To get the workaholic Noelle some rest, you suggest that the two of you have some tea and let loose a little...

19068.Name: Gift and Intent
19068.Desc: Noelle has, as is her wont, extended a helping hand to Bea, who is facing a bit of a romantic quandary. After some discussion, you decide to use a gift to help Bea get her feelings across...

19069.Name: Gift and Intent
19069.Desc: Noelle has, as is her wont, extended a helping hand to Bea, who is facing a bit of a romantic quandary. After some discussion, you decide to use a gift to help Bea get her feelings across...

20068.Name: Sorry, Timmie!
20068.Desc: Timmie seems to have a bone to pick with you over some matter. Perhaps Sister Grace might know a way to help resolve things between you two...

20069.Name: Floral Fresh
20069.Desc: Flowers don't stay fresh for long. Flora, the owner of the Floral Whisper, has been thinking of ways to preserve them better...

20070.Name: Fresh Flora
20070.Desc: To help Flora ascertain the effectiveness of putting plants in cold storage, you must head to Dragonspine once again to retrieve the flowers buried in the snow...

20071.Name: Fresh Flora
20071.Desc: To help Flora ascertain the effectiveness of putting plants in cold storage, you must head to Dragonspine once again to retrieve the flowers buried in the snow...

20072.Name: Fresh Flora
20072.Desc: To help Flora ascertain the effectiveness of putting plants in cold storage, you must head to Dragonspine once again to retrieve the flowers buried in the snow...

20073.Name: Emergency Supplies
20073.Desc: Riese is preparing emergency supplies to protect some reckless adventurers from getting in trouble on Dragonspine...

20104.Name: Cleanup At Dawn II
20104.Desc: At the behest of head housemaid Adelinde, maids Moco and Hillie have begun cleaning up. However, they seem to have run into a spot of trouble...

20511.Name: Miracle Medicine
20511.Desc: Anthony requested a prescription from a master physician in Liyue Harbor that can be used to heal Anna.

20512.Name: Miracle Medicine
20512.Desc: Anthony requested a prescription from a master physician in Liyue Harbor that can be used to heal Anna.

20513.Name: Miracle Medicine
20513.Desc: Anthony requested a prescription from a master physician in Liyue Harbor that can be used to heal Anna.

20514.Name: Recuperating From a Severe Illness
20514.Desc: As Anna has been recovering from her illness, she's finally started playing all around the city again. However, Anthony can't seem to find her anywhere...

20515.Name: Recuperating From a Severe Illness
20515.Desc: As Anna has been recovering from her illness, she's finally started playing all around the city again. However, Anthony can't seem to find her anywhere...

20516.Name: Recuperating From a Severe Illness
20516.Desc: As Anna has been recovering from her illness, she's finally started playing all around the city again. However, Anthony can't seem to find her anywhere...

20517.Name: A Surprise Gift
20517.Desc: Rudolf wants to send a gift to his wife, Jilliana, but has no idea what to give her. He's at a loss about what to do...

20518.Name: A Commission from "That Guy"
20518.Desc: After taking care of Jilliana's matter, Vile came again to inform you that "That Guy" has another commission for you.

20519.Name: A Commission from "That Guy"
20519.Desc: After taking care of Jilliana's matter, Vile came again to inform you that "That Guy" has another commission for you.

20520.Name: Only Half-Frozen
20520.Desc: Despite being well on the way towards freezing to death, Tommy the adventurer is concerned about one thing only: his incomplete commission...

20521.Name: Eat It While It's Hot
20521.Desc: The aroma of food wafts toward you from a camp below Dragonspine — but Chef Harris seems anxious about something...

20600.Name: Tales of Winter
20600.Desc: In Mondstadt, the Fatui member Viktor is recruiting people to join their cause. This may be a good opportunity to pry into what the Fatui is up to.

20601.Name: A Fine Opportunity?
20601.Desc: Even in the midst of the storm, Cyrus of the Adventurers' Guild seems to be gearing up for action...

20602.Name: Not to be Missed
20602.Desc: The storm has subsided, but Cyrus seems displeased...

20603.Name: Time Waits For No Man
20603.Desc: Mondstadt's crisis has passed, but Cyrus seems... unhappy?

20700.Name: Reliable Helper
20700.Desc: The Snezhnayan merchant Tsarevich is looking for a dependable person to help him resolve a few problems.

20701.Name: A Returning Customer
20701.Desc: Siegfria can't stop thinking about the delectable Jade Parcels. Oh how she wants to taste it again...

20702.Name: Question and Answer
20702.Desc: Swan does everything by the book — specifically, by the Knights of Favonius Handbook. Previously, Swan wouldn't ask anything of the Traveler, who was not a Knight then. Now that the Traveler is an Honorary Knight, Swan will sometimes quiz the Traveler concerning the contents of the Handbook.

20703.Name: Leaves on the Wind
20703.Desc: Edith wants to write a new book about Anemo, but she's looking for some inspiration...

20740.Name: Flighty Flora... and Flora
20740.Desc: Flora from the flower shop in Mondstadt is quite upset... It seems that many of her flowers have suddenly been blown away by the wind. She's looking for somebody who could help her...

20741.Name: Mondstadt and its Archon
20741.Desc: Now that Mondstadt has been spared from disaster, Sister Grace would like to offer her thanks to the Anemo Archon for its protection of the city.

20743.Name: Windrise, Windfall
20743.Desc: The recent storms have been affecting business at Dawn Winery, so Elzer is trying his best to come up with ideas to get things back in order...

22009.Name: A Little Raid
22009.Desc: Soraya is fed up with those Treasure Hoarders constantly digging up relics. She's looking for someone who can help put a stop to them once and for all.

22114.Name: So-Called Work
22114.Desc: After having made one mistake too many at work, Linling is in danger of losing her job...

22200.Name: A Bottomless Appetite
22200.Desc: Yicheng, who patrols Feiyun Slope, seems to have grown so hungry that his stomach can no longer bear it...

22500.Name: Growing Pains
22500.Desc: Little Lulu has been unhappy lately. She seems to be troubled by a certain something...

22501.Name: The Essence of Poetry
22501.Desc: Qingzhou has found a muse in the rain of meteorites, and simply must go to the place where they made landfall to compose a verse or two...

22701.Name: The Sparrow Studies the Blade
22701.Desc: Sun Yu is seeking the guidance of the adepti in Jueyun Karst, but seems to require some help first...

40000.Name: Liyue: Theater Mechanicus
40000.Desc: Ruijin from Liyue Harbor is promoting a new "game"...

41111.Name: Unknown Star
41111.Desc: Katheryne of the Mondstadt Adventurers' Guild seems to have something to tell you.

41112.Name: The Crisis Deepens
41112.Desc: As your investigation proceeds, you gradually realize that there is some mysterious power hidden within these meteorites. In order to help the victims regain consciousness, you and your comrades begin to dispose of meteorites throughout the land...

41113.Name: What the Skies Conceal, the Water Reveals
41113.Desc: Apart from the spate of unconsciousness caused by the meteorites, the appearance of the Fatui has also aroused your suspicions. Fortunately, the arrival of the astrologist Mona has given your efforts a much-needed boost. With the help of her mystical scrying techniques, you begin to delve into these mysteries...

41114.Name: Where Ancient Stars Align
41114.Desc: The meteorites that have rained down were once, in fact, part of someone's constellation. Why did this ancient array of stars fall from the sky? What goal were their extinguished flames chasing? Armed with the courage to face the answers, you march onward.

41120.Name: That Which Fell From the Sky
41120.Desc: Due to the constant descent of meteorites from the sky, it has become too unsafe to go outside. Sister Grace is very worried about those people who linger out there in the wild...

41121.Name: Good Hunter Express
41121.Desc: The Good Hunter has a special order that needs sending out...

41122.Name: To Each Their Duty
41122.Desc: Even though rocks are falling from the skies, some Knights of Favonius are still attending to their duties outside the city. Huffman is rather worried about these knights...

41123.Name: Contingencies
41123.Desc: Huffman is currently so busy with matters concerning the fallen meteorites, that he barely has time for anything else...

41124.Name: "That Guy"'s Scheme
41124.Desc: The fallen meteorites have turned Mondstadt upside down, inside and out. But it seems that the mysterious Vile is looking for people to help her out with a little something...

41125.Name: Meteorites and Adventure
41125.Desc: Jack from the Adventurers' Guild seems to have some ideas on what to do about those fallen meteorites...

41126.Name: Trouble With Letters
41126.Desc: Due to the meteor shower, Jiayi's plans to return home to see his family have been canceled yet again. He is looking for someone to send a letter to Qingce Village...

41127.Name: A Mysterious Loss
41127.Desc: Many meteorites have landed outside the city of Mondstadt, wreaking havoc everywhere. Viktor appears to have lost something important, and is talking to himself, flummoxed...

41130.Name: The Siege of Qingce
41130.Desc: The Millelith soldier Jinglun is fretting about how to defeat the monsters around Qingce Village...

41131.Name: Unlimited Opportunity
41131.Desc: Ivanovich is getting ideas about what business might be done regarding those fallen meteorites...

41135.Name: Thoughts Carried On the Wind
41135.Desc: The meteor shower out in the wild seems to have left Godwin all in a fluster...

41141.Name: Wangshu Take-Away
41141.Desc: Wangshu Inn has a special order that needs sending out...

41142.Name: Wanmin Fresh
41142.Desc: Wanmin Restaurant has taken a custom order that now awaits delivery...

41143.Desc: The Good Hunter has a special order that needs sending out...

41159.Desc: Wangshu Inn has a special order that needs sending out...

41160.Name: Wanmin Fresh
41160.Desc: Wanmin Restaurant has taken a custom order that now awaits delivery...

41170.Name: Fly High
41170.Desc: The adventurer Hughes is a wind glider fanatic. To that end, he travels the world, constantly polishing his gliding skills. Recently, he seems to have discovered several prime gliding spots...

41210.Name: Festering Desire
41210.Desc: After your journey up Dragonspine, you and Paimon prepare to head back to the adventurer camp in the foothills to have a look.

41211.Name: Archon's Rival
41211.Desc: As Albedo suspected, this sword can absorb power to display a facsimile of "growth." This rare ability has caused it to catch the eye of certain parties with ulterior motives.

41212.Name: Raiders Amidst Snow Mist
41212.Desc: All proceeds smoothly. You plan to search for Albedo to discuss the changes the sword has undergone further.

41213.Name: Uninvited Guests
41213.Desc: Many unexpected things have happened on this mountain. A mysterious hidden camp, suddenly-appearing thieves, uninvited enemies... This sword seems to have brought you into the thick of all this weirdness. So long as it remains in your hands, trouble will always follow in its wake — with such troubles including those who have come to take the sword, and new monsters heretofore unseen.

41214.Name: Afterword
41214.Desc: After a long battle, the sword that has, at last, completed its growth has a new place to be.

41311.Name: The Origin of the Lanterns
41311.Desc: On the day of the first full moon each year, the people of Liyue celebrate Lantern Rite. At nighttime, everyone in Liyue releases Xiao Lanterns and the Mingxiao Lantern into the bright night sky. Each Xiao Lantern contains a piece of Plaustrite that makes it float, and people hang wish sticks from them, which carry their hearts' desires in written or painted form. The lanterns slowly fly away, carrying the hope that the light they emit might guide the souls of Liyue's faithful protectors home, that they might return and be reunited with their people once more. You and Paimon arrive in Liyue as the festival is in full swing, preparing to enjoy yourselves...

41312.Name: Currents Deep Beneath the Lanterns
41312.Desc: The highlight of Lantern Rite is the release of the giant Mingxiao Lantern into the sky, and this year's Mingxiao Lantern is supposed to be a sight well worth the wait. The Plaustrite that will lift the lantern into the air is the largest in twenty years! For this special occasion, the merchants of Liyue have set up the Xiao Market to help gather the materials needed to build the lantern. When you arrive at the Xiao Market, one of the event organizers, Wang'ya, seems to have something to say to you...

41313.Name: Light Upon the Sea
41313.Desc: Lantern Rite is still ongoing. With the help of Xiao, Kaeya, and the Millelith, you have foiled a "plot" that has left you not knowing whether to laugh or cry and have succeeded in bringing the foolish criminal behind it to justice and handing them over to the Millelith. Today, you prepare to go to Wangshu Inn to report the results of the matter to Xiao, as you agreed...

41331.Name: Qingce's Lanterns
41331.Desc: Something seems to be bothering Granny Ruoxin from Qingce Village...

41332.Name: Keeping Wanmin's Patrons Fed
41332.Desc: Once again, it's the Lantern Rite — and once again, Wanmin Restaurant's Chef Mao is busier than ever...

41333.Name: Iron Ingot Meets Ziwei
41333.Desc: Iron Ingot from Liyue Harbor seems to be troubled about something...

41334.Name: Lantern Rite, Big Business?
41334.Desc: Mr. Zhu seems to want to use the Lantern Rite to pick his business up a little...

41335.Name: Verses and Vistas of Lantern Rite (Part I)
41335.Desc: The artist Vermeer is puzzling over how to capture the Lantern Rite in a painting...

41336.Name: Outspoken Linling
41336.Desc: Linling from Liyue Harbor seems to be troubled by something...

41337.Name: Yesteryear's Lanterns and the Guhua of Today
41337.Desc: Sun Yu and Little Que'er seem to want to release a Xiao Lantern...

41338.Name: A Festive First Adventure
41338.Desc: Tiantian of the Liyue Adventurers' Guild seems to have been working on something...

41340.Name: A Very Festive Problem
41340.Desc: Bubu Pharmacy's Herbalist Gui is racking his brains about something...

41341.Name: Little Lantern, Little Wish
41341.Desc: Mengmeng seems to be troubled by something...

41342.Name: Hammer and Wrench
41342.Desc: Wrench Wang from Liyue Harbor seems to be looking for help with some matters...

41343.Name: Mondstadters in Liyue
41343.Desc: Freki and Geri are getting a little homesick...

41357.Name: The Illumiscreen: I
41357.Desc: Brother Qian from the Liyue Adventurers' Guild is inviting people to play a certain game...

41358.Name: The Illumiscreen: II
41358.Desc: Brother Qian from the Liyue Adventurers' Guild is still inviting people to try playing with the Illumiscreen...

41359.Name: The Illumiscreen: III
41359.Desc: Brother Qian from the Liyue Adventurers' Guild is still inviting people to try playing with the Illumiscreen...

41401.Name: Kurious Kamera
41401.Desc: A certain special Kamera is currently causing Ji Tong some grief...

41402.Name: Perfect Shot
41402.Desc: Ji Tong from Liyue Harbor seems to have found a way to fix that Kamera of his...

41410.Name: Ode to Flower and Cloud
41410.Desc: When you've got some leisure time, how about taking a stroll through Mondstadt's streets and seeing if there's anything to do?

41411.Name: Missive of Cloud and Fog
41411.Desc: As Venti's all-important assistant, you are to go out with him to collect the love poetry written by the people of Mondstadt. However, the citizenry has various troubles of their own, even during such a festive time as this.

41412.Name: Realm of Fog and Wind
41412.Desc: You and Venti keep pushing on for the sake of some good wine. Cold corners, perilous places, strange sites... who knows what incidents await the two of you? Even more interestingly, you begin to realize that there is no common understanding of what a "Windblume" is.

41413.Name: Dream of Wind and Flowers
41413.Desc: On account of your contributions to Mondstadt, you have been chosen as this year's Windblume Star. As such, you will be making a Windblume offering to the Anemo Archon, Barbatos, on behalf of the whole of Mondstadt. That said, what on earth is a Windblume?

41421.Name: Life Flows On (I)
41421.Desc: The water source near the winery has become bitter for no apparent reason. The Adventurers' Guild hopes for your cooperation in resolving this matter.

41422.Name: Life Flows On (II)
41422.Desc: After having helped Endora for this period of time, you are finally ready to cut to the heart of this problem.

70000.Name: Windblume Research Report
70000.Desc: The ever-studious researcher, Sayid from Sumeru, has become intrigued by the Windblume Festival.

70001.Name: The Sound of Discord
70001.Desc: Vile has caught wind of some concerning news and would like you to go and investigate.

70003.Name: Those Hard-to-Reach Places
70003.Desc: Knight of Favonius Aramis is worried about the flower petals blowing all over the place...

70007.Name: "Quiet, please, this is a library!"
70007.Desc: Ella Musk is trying to study in the library, but it seems something is disrupting her...

70008.Name: Windbrew
70008.Desc: Margaret from The Cat's Tail seems to be planning something...

70009.Name: Windblumes and Snowflakes
70009.Desc: Viktor seems to have run into a small issue during the Windblume Festival.

70010.Name: Adventurers in Windblume
70010.Desc: Iris, who has set up shop at the Dragonspine base camp, seems to want some help...

70102.Name: The Festering Fang
70102.Desc: You picked up a strange dragon tooth while adventuring in Dragonspine. Perhaps you should ask around and see if someone knows anything more about it...

70104.Name: The Great Mountain Survey
70104.Desc: The environmentalist Esther and the expedition team with her were set upon by monsters while performing a mountain survey, with the larger part of her survey beacons being lost in the process. She is currently looking for someone who can get them back for her...

70106.Name: Ah, Fresh Meat!
70106.Desc: Harris, the chef at the foothill camp, has received inspiration from an ancient recipe and would like to create an all-new gourmet dish. For this, he first requires 10 servings of Chilled Meat...

70107.Name: Low-Temperature Warning
70107.Desc: Iris has a warning for you regarding Dragonspine's low temperatures...

70108.Name: The Great Mountain Survey II
70108.Desc: Though the beacons have all been placed, Esther remains unable to measure Dragonspine's true height, seemingly due to having insufficient beacons. To resolve the issue, she is looking for someone who can help her plant a beacon directly at the mountain's summit...

70121.Name: A Land Entombed
70121.Desc: You discover a strange journal in the mountains that tells of the secrets of a certain kingdom. Perhaps someone at the camp may know more about this journal...

70123.Name: Lost in the Snow
70123.Desc: Joel asks you to ahead into the mountain to look for his father, who has yet to return from an adventure of his own...

70141.Name: In the Mountains
70141.Desc: At the adventurer camp, Iris informs you that there seems to be some bizarrely hard ice blocking the paths into the mountain...

70650.Name: Knight of the Realm
70650.Desc: The Knight of Favonius, Hertha, seems to want a word with you...

70651.Name: Mine Craft
70651.Desc: Mining is not an easy task... But perhaps Mondstadt's blacksmith, Wagner, might have some tips for you...

70652.Name: The Path of the Treasure-Seeker, Part I
70652.Desc: You meet a "treasure-seeker" named Ulman out in the wild. He says that he's looking for a capable "partner" to help him out...

70653.Name: Vishaps and Where to Find Them
70653.Desc: Recently, a lot of unusual phenomena have been occurring all over Liyue. According to some, they may be related to a monster depicted in ancient texts, the Geovishap. Katheryne of the Liyue Adventurers' Guild posted an urgent commission, calling adventurers to investigate the irregularities.

70654.Name: Floral Freefall
70654.Desc: During the Windblume Festival, the area around Mondstadt will play host to all sorts of interesting activities. The Knights of Favonius' Lizzie would like to introduce you to one of the highlights of this event — "Floral Freefall."

70655.Name: Mountainous Summons
70655.Desc: The hilichurls of Dadaupa Gorge have grown unusually active. The Adventurers' Guild's scholar-adventurer, Dr. Livingstone, is currently investigating the Gorge. Perhaps you can lend her some help.

70656.Name: Peculiar Wonderland
70656.Desc: Plauen of the Adventurers' Guild would like to introduce you to a mysterious Domain in the wilds of Mondstadt.

70657.Name: Bullseye Balloons
70657.Desc: During the Windblume Festival, the area around Mondstadt will play host to all sorts of interesting activities. The Knights of Favonius' Lizzie would like to introduce you to one of the highlights of this event — "Bullseye Balloons."

70658.Name: Ballads of Breeze
70658.Desc: During the Windblume Festival, the area around Mondstadt will play host to all sorts of interesting activities. The Knights of Favonius' Lizzie would like to introduce you to one of the highlights of this event — "Ballads of Breeze."

70700.Name: Helen's Special Blend
70700.Desc: Helen from Mondstadt needs 10 Sweet Flowers.

70701.Name: Glory's Wish
70701.Desc: Glory from Mondstadt needs three sets of Dandelion Seeds.

70706.Desc: Timmie from Mondstadt needs ten servings of Wheat.

70707.Desc: Alfred from Mondstadt needs three Windwheel Asters.

70708.Desc: Alfred from Mondstadt needs three Cecilias.

70709.Desc: Manly Jack needs three Chicken-Mushroom Skewers.

70711.Desc: Manly Jack needs three servings of Mondstadt Grilled Fish.

70713.Desc: Springvale's Brook requires six servings of Raw Meat.

70714.Name: Brook the Carnivore
70714.Desc: Springvale's Brook requires six servings of Fowl.

70800.Name: Flavor of the Month
70800.Desc: Brook from Springvale wants to create a new dish during the Windblume Festival.

70801.Name: Question and Answer
70801.Desc: Swan does everything by the book — specifically, by the Knights of Favonius Handbook. Previously, Swan wouldn't ask anything of the Traveler, who was not a Knight then. Now that the Traveler is an Honorary Knight, Swan will sometimes quiz the Traveler concerning the contents of the Handbook.

70810.Name: Equivalent Exchange
70810.Desc: Viktor is looking for someone to help him gather some local specialties...

70812.Name: Lingering Malady
70812.Desc: Due to the storm that swept through the city, the posters and signboards of many shops have been blown off to the rooftops and city walls of Mondstadt. Aramis of the Knights of Favonius is currently mulling over how he might retrieve them...

70813.Name: Thief-Catcher
70813.Desc: The storm has just ended, and Cyrus from the Adventurers' Guild is currently planning to clear the Treasure Hoarders out...

70814.Name: ...What Do Adventurers Do Again?
70814.Desc: At Lan's direction, Tiantian of the Adventurers' Guild has been put in charge of distributing commissions, but she has no idea what sort of commissions she should be giving out to adventurers...

70815.Name: Will of Stone
70815.Desc: Millelith soldier Jiayi wants to send a gift to his daughter, Little Liu, but he has no time to return to Qingce Village, and as such is looking for someone to help him out...

70816.Name: Solo Venture
70816.Desc: While investigating the movements of monsters at the Thousand Winds Temple, Jack was discovered due to his recklessness and attacked. Jack somehow made it back to Mondstadt, but he seems to have left something important behind at the Temple...

70821.Name: After the Storm
70821.Desc: After Dvalin was cleansed, access to Stormterror's Lair has been restored. Wagner would like to go there to look for precious Crystal Ore...

70822.Name: A Quiet Day in Liyue Harbor
70822.Desc: Nervous An, busy at the harbor, is looking for someone to help to ease the nerves of guests from other nations...

70823.Name: Blackcliff Woes
70823.Desc: The Chasm remains closed by order of the Ministry of Civil Affairs, which has put the Blackcliff Forge out of action since. Manager Kuan is troubled over this matter...

70824.Name: Cleanup At Dawn
70824.Desc: After the storm, head housemaid Adelinde is preparing to render the Dawn Winery spick and span on the inside and out, but things aren't going so smoothly...

70825.Name: In the Aftermath
70825.Desc: Huffman has his hands full with the cleanup work that followed the storm...

71005.Name: Nine Pillars of Peace
71005.Desc: Nine stone pillars stand stoic near Cuijue Slope. They seem to hide a certain secret...

71006.Name: Luhua Landscape
71006.Desc: Vermeer, an artist who is looking for inspirational material near Luhua Pool, seems to have hit a snag, and is looking for help...

71008.Name: A Little Game
71008.Desc: You met a strange person on Mt. Tianheng who is looking for someone to play hide-and-seek with him...

71011.Name: Trails in Tianqiu
71011.Desc: There is a strange tablet in Tianqiu Valley that seems to relate some of the valley's history...

71012.Name: Time and Wind
71012.Desc: You reach an uninhabited island across the sea, which is home to an enigmatic sundial. Who knows what secret it holds?

71014.Name: The Ocean Pearl
71014.Desc: A mysterious ship has dropped anchor outside Liyue Harbor. The ship appears to be quite luxurious, all the more reason to hop right on board...

71018.Name: A Lone Ship In Guyun
71018.Desc: A heavily armed ship of unknown origins has stopped outside Guyun Stone Forest. You hop right on board to investigate...

71020.Name: Pressing Deadlines
71020.Desc: Clerk Zhao is so swamped with work that she can't even get a moment to herself. It seems she could use some assistance...

71022.Name: No Restoring This Past Land of Beauty
71022.Desc: Zhiping of the Adventurers' Guild seems to be investigating the earthquakes and strange monster movements in Tianqiu Valley...

71033.Name: Verses and Vistas of Lantern Rite (Part II)
71033.Desc: Painter Vermeer seems to be looking for Qingzhou...

71650.Name: Ministry Missions
71650.Desc: Ms. Yu, a resource manager from the Ministry of Civil Affairs, has something to say to you...

71651.Name: The Vishaps Lie Dormant, but the Enigma Lingers Still
71651.Desc: After a sustained effort, you seem to have scared the Geovishaps into submission and the disturbances across the land seem to have subsided. However, the reason for their re-emergence and rampage remains a mystery...

71700.Name: Let's Make A Flower Garland!
71700.Desc: Liyue Harbor's Changchang needs three Silk Flowers.

71701.Name: Herbalist's Forage
71701.Desc: Liyue Harbor's Herbalist Gui needs three Qingxin.

71702.Desc: Liyue Harbor's Herbalist Gui needs three Violetgrass.

71703.Desc: Liyue Harbor's Herbalist Gui needs 10 Sweet Flowers.

71704.Desc: Liyue Harbor's Herbalist Gui needs ten Mints.

71705.Desc: Wangshu Inn's Smiley Yanxiao needs two Sausages.

71706.Name: Smiley's Selections
71706.Desc: Wangshu Inn's Smiley Yanxiao needs two Hams.

71707.Name: Smiley's Selections
71707.Desc: Wangshu Inn's Smiley Yanxiao needs two strips of Bacon.

71708.Name: Hanfeng's Iron-Mongering
71708.Desc: Hanfeng from Qingce Village needs ten Iron Chunks.

71710.Desc: Geri needs three bowls of Radish Veggie Soup.

71714.Desc: Yi Zhu needs a serving of Almond Tofu.

71802.Name: An Adeptal Summons
71802.Desc: If you wish to meet Cloud Retainer again, you must prepare a food offering...

71803.Name: The Adventurers' Guild's Affairs
71803.Desc: Lan seems to be fretting over some of the commissions that the Adventurers' Guild has undertaken...

71804.Name: Necessary Procedures
71804.Desc: The storm in Liyue harbor has passed, and all aspects of life within the city are slowly undergoing changes... For Ivanovich, this means working hard to adapt to said changes...

71805.Name: Words Worth Their Weight in Mora
71805.Desc: The recent crisis that beset Liyue Harbor has reinvigorated interest in history. Wanwen Bookhouse has seen a resurgence in business as a result, and its owner Jifang is on the verge of being overwhelmed...

71807.Name: Changchang's Little Friend
71807.Desc: Changchang from Liyue Harbor is looking for someone to get some food for a little puppy...

71808.Name: The Secret of Nantianmen
71808.Desc: Jiayi from Liyue Harbor has gotten himself tangled up in more troublesome affairs, and is looking for some help...

71809.Name: An Ode to Yonder City
71809.Desc: Liyue's crisis has settled down, but it has brought a wave of change to the city. The poet Qingzhou would like to capture these shifts in verse...

71810.Name: Endless Research
71810.Desc: You meet Alrani, whom you once saved from a cage, in Liyue Harbor. She still seems to want to investigate something...

71811.Name: Snapshots
71811.Desc: Xu of the Feiyun Commerce Guild is currently puzzling over a device known as a Kamera...

71812.Name: Tianqiu Treasure Trail
71812.Desc: Lan of the Liyue Harbor Adventurers' Guild seems to be troubled by something...

71813.Name: Return of the Jade Chamber?
71813.Desc: You learn from a Millelith named Kun that there are plans to rebuild the previously destroyed Jade Chamber and that some small preparations to that end are already taking place...

71814.Name: Fishing For Jade
71814.Desc: In the aftermath of the collision between the Jade Chamber and That Which Lies in the Deep, the sea remains dotted with floating fragments of the Jade Chamber. The Millelith soldier Kun is currently looking for help with the cleanup work...

71815.Name: Guests in Qingce
71815.Desc: Wang'ya has something to say to you at Wangshu Inn...

71816.Name: Lantern of the Wayfarer
71816.Desc: While most people from Liyue are enjoying the Lantern Rite, guard-for-hire Huangshan is currently in a bit of a fix...

71817.Name: Yanxiao's Crazy Kitchen
71817.Desc: Smiley Yanxiao from Wangshu Inn seems to be struggling with his workload during the Lantern Rite...

71818.Name: The Gift of a Lantern
71818.Desc: Ms. Bai from Qingce Village seems to be making some preparations...

71819.Name: City of Chores
71819.Desc: Wang'ya from Liyue Harbor seems to be troubled by something...

71820.Name: Wangshu Once Again
71820.Desc: Something is bothering Verr Goldet, boss of the Wangshu Inn...

71821.Name: Where the Light Wanes
71821.Desc: While everyone else is lifting their eyes up to the lovely sight of Xiao Lanterns in the sky, Millelith soldier Hongyu is having a headache...

71822.Name: When Scholar and Legends Meet
71822.Desc: The scholar Soraya seems to be investigating something in Mt. Tianheng...

71823.Name: Guardians of the Countryside
71823.Desc: The festival is in full swing, but Zhi of Qingce Village is trying to remedy a herb-related predicament...

71824.Name: Promises Remembered as Lanterns Rise
71824.Desc: Wangshu Inn's chef, Smiley Yanxiao, seems to have a lot on his plate right now...

90001.Name: Quest Editor Test
90001.Desc: This quest was made to test the Quest Editor, to see if the output data accepts the parameter and executes the release process normally.

10120.Name: Shadow of the Past
10120.Desc: Master Jean has a special task for you. Head to the Knights of Favonius Headquarters to find out more.

10121.Name: Speech and Etiquette
10121.Desc: You successfully locate Eula, who agrees to teach you the customs of the Lawrence Clan. To fulfill the task given to you by Master Jean, it seems you will need to undergo quite the rigorous training program...

10122.Name: Through the Motions, to the Heart
10122.Desc: You get through the aristocratic conduct training, albeit with some hiccups along the way. During the training, you believe you may have discovered what shapes Eula's personality. You say goodbye to Eula and decide to act — first, you will procure a greeting gift, then you will meet with Schubert once more.

11008.Name: A Teapot to Call Home: Part I
11008.Desc: The crisis looming over Liyue Harbor has calmed, and it's business as usual in the city. However, Madame Ping, the flower-admirer from Yujing Terrace, seems to have something more to discuss with you...

11120.Name: Strange Sights, Stolen Souls
11120.Desc: Katheryne of the Adventurers' Guild in Liyue Harbor has a new commission for you. You and Paimon decide to find out what it's all about.

11121.Name: Truth in the Stones
11121.Desc: You arrive at the mine, the scene of the incident, and begin your investigation. A series of clues makes clear that there is nothing ordinary about this disappearance. What is the connection between the mysterious person behind this incident and the missing miners? Where did the missing miners disappear to? You have to know the truth.

11122.Name: Shifting Earth and Lost Threads Come to Light
11122.Desc: The evidence at the mining site suggests that the miners followed the road north. You follow the trail, gradually closing in on them.

11123.Name: Amidst Chaos, the Rock Is Unmoved
11123.Desc: Finally, you reach Nantianmen. A curious ancient tree has quietly stood here throughout the ages, bearing witness to all that has come to pass. To rescue the miners and solve this puzzle once and for all, you proceed to the ancient site that holds all the answers...

19081.Name: Studious Maid
19081.Desc: Noelle is usually brimming with energy, but recently she has been cooped up in the library, worrying about something or other...

19082.Name: Journey to Liyue
19082.Desc: Noelle reveals to you that she is very anxious about the Knights of Favonius selection exam. At your suggestion, she decides to join you on a trip to Liyue to relieve her stress...

19083.Name: While the Millelith Stands Guard
19083.Desc: Noelle is mistaken for a Knight of Favonius several times over the course of the trip. After things have calmed down a little, you decide to see what Noelle could learn from the Millelith down by the harbor.

19084.Name: A Knight's Journey Through Liyue
19084.Desc: Noelle is mistaken for a Knight of Favonius several times over the course of the trip. After things have calmed down a little, you decide to stop by Third-Round Knockout and take a short break.

19085.Name: Adventurer's Entrance Exam
19085.Desc: Noelle reveals to you that she is very anxious about the Knights of Favonius selection exam. At your suggestion, the two of you head to the Adventurers' Guild, hoping to get some extra exam experience.

19086.Name: Adventurer's Entrance Exam
19086.Desc: After fully understanding Noelle's reasons for seeking him out, an elated and excited Cyrus decides to put you both through his new exam at the highest difficulty level.

19087.Name: Adventurer's Entrance Exam
19087.Desc: After fully understanding Noelle's reasons for seeking him out, an elated and excited Cyrus decides to put you both through his new exam at the highest difficulty level.

19090.Name: Noelle Rides Out
19090.Desc: Noelle reveals to you that she is very anxious about the Knights of Favonius selection exam. At your suggestion, she decides to emulate the knights she knows in an attempt to overcome her sense of unease.

19091.Name: Substitute Acting Grand Master Noelle
19091.Desc: Noelle decides to emulate Jean by returning to Mondstadt and helping the citizens with their problems.

19092.Name: Noelle the Intelligence Operative
19092.Desc: Noelle decides to emulate Kaeya by heading to the Angel's Share and attempting to gather intel on any threats to Mondstadt's security.

19101.Name: The Cat's Tail's Bartender
19101.Desc: They say that there's a popular bartender at The Cat's Tail.

19102.Name: To Catch a Kitten
19102.Desc: Searching for three kitties in Mondstadt might not be the easiest thing in the world...

19103.Name: A Special Base Drink
19103.Desc: Diona would like to go to Dadaupa Gorge to secure a certain special "base drink."

19104.Name: The Shadow Over Dadaupa
19104.Desc: Getting deep into Dadaupa Gorge might require a cunning plan...

19105.Name: Samachurl Herbal Soup
19105.Desc: According to Diona, the herbal soup made by samachurls can possibly be used to make an antidote to alcohol.

19106.Name: Special Cocktailing Condiments
19106.Desc: Diona wants to look for some special flavoring for her cocktail.

19107.Name: Exchanging Pointers
19107.Desc: In order to learn the tricks of a professional mixologist, Diona decides to exchange pointers with Connor.

70006.Desc: You go with Ella Musk to communicate with the hilichurls. Perhaps this might be the start of a new friendship...?

70024.Desc: The Adventurers' Guild has issued a new commission, and it seems to be related to a certain "Unusual Hilichurl"...?

70025.Name: The Lost Hilichurl
70025.Desc: The unusual fellow may have gotten away in the end, but at least the merchant route is safe again.

70143.Name: When the Trail Goes Cold
70143.Desc: The Mondstadt Adventurers' Guild appears to be recruiting adventurers for a new and ambitious adventure...

70144.Name: Chilled to the Bone
70144.Desc: An unusual cold air current has suddenly appeared on Dragonspine, and Iris is looking for someone to investigate...

70659.Name: A Timeless Classic
70659.Desc: Gygax from Mondstadt seems to be trying to drum up some interest in his game.

71652.Name: Mr. Melancholy
71652.Desc: Yingzhu of the Adventurers' Guild has been having dealings with a scholar from the Sumeru Academia, but things seem to be going downhill, fast...

71653.Name: We Meet Again, Mr. Melancholy
71653.Desc: After some painstaking gathering, it's time to report back to Hosseini.

71654.Name: A Teapot to Call Home: Part II
71654.Desc: The crisis looming over Liyue Harbor has calmed, and it's business as usual in the city. However, Madame Ping, the flower-admirer from Yujing Terrace, seems to have something more to discuss with you...

2000.Name: A Path Through the Storm
2000.Desc: You share your feelings with Paimon before embarking on the next phase of your journey.

2001.Name: The Crux Clash
2001.Desc: After meeting some of the contestants, you reckon that this will be a milk run. Still, your ticket to Inazuma is at stake here. Best not to let your guard down during the tournament.

2002.Name: Follow the Wind
2002.Desc: The grand final of the Crux Clash is about to begin, and you will soon meet your opponent. Victory is but one step away...

40010.Name: Mysterious Islands: Journey to the Unknown
40010.Desc: Long time no Klee — let's go visit her at the Knights of Favonius headquarters!

40011.Name: Summer Vacation: Proceed With Caution
40011.Desc: Though these islands seem completely cut off from the rest of the world, they are somehow chock-full of hidden secrets and mysterious mechanisms. The party settles here for now and starts to get a taste of island life in the summer...

40012.Name: Dodo-King of the Sea: Lying in Wait
40012.Desc: The party learns from Barbara that their surroundings seem to be changing once again. Where will the trail lead this time? How many stories lay buried among these islands? And who know what the next surprise will be?

40013.Name: The Final Riddle: A Secret Uncovered
40013.Desc: Thanks to a joint effort, the party finds the key to solving the final riddle. The truth behind these islands is now within reach, but Klee seems to be more anxious than ever. What is the truth that has quietly sat in wait all this time?

40016.Name: Archipelago Quest 1
40016.Desc: The billowing waves of summer competition are just around the corner. Full speed ahead, mateys! Failure is not an option!

71655.Name: Idle Teapot Talk
71655.Desc: Tubby, the teapot spirit in your Serenitea Pot, seems to have something to say to you...

71829.Name: A Dish Beyond Mortal Ken
71829.Desc: Something seems to be bothering Wangshu Inn's Smiley Yanxiao...

79000.Name: They Who Hear the Sea
79000.Desc: You discover a strange conch shell on Twinning Isle in the Golden Apple Archipelago. The sounds that come from within seem to hint at something...

79001.Name: The Winding Homeward Way
79001.Desc: You meet a strange Seelie on Minacious Isle...

79002.Name: Who Wields the Wild Wind?
79002.Desc: No-one knows why, but this island seems to be forever affected by strange weather conditions...

79003.Name: From Outer Lands
79003.Desc: You discover a strange wrecked ship on a nameless island. But the question is, where did this ship come from?

79004.Name: The Other Side of Isle and Sea
79004.Desc: You discover a strange mural in the Golden Apple Archipelago...
